config_schema.ops:
Ordered list of operations applied to the working DataFrame. Each op is {op: <name>, ...op-specific keys, as?: <publish_name>}. Supported ops:
• window_bucket {time_col, interval_ms, out_col}
  Floor a timestamp into integer buckets of size interval_ms.

• time_slice {time_col, out_col, on_miss?, windows: [{name,start,end}]}
  Label rows with a phase string based on which window they fall in.
  start/end accept {context.x} or any ref grammar; missing rows get on_miss.

• groupby_agg {by, aggs: {col: agg, ...}}
  Standard pandas groupby + agg, returns a flat reset_index frame.

• pivot {index, columns, values, aggfunc?}
  DataFrame.pivot_table; column names cast to str; fill_value=0.

• rolling {window, col, agg, out_col?}
  Rolling window aggregation (mean/sum/min/max/std/...) with
  min_periods=1.

• derive {out_col, expr}
  Vectorised DataFrame.eval expression (no Python branching).

• apply_expr {out_col, expr}
  Per-row Python expression evaluated with the row as locals.
  Slower; use only when `derive` cannot express the logic.

• rename {mapping: {old_name: new_name, ...}}
  Rename columns in place.

• lifecycle_event {group_by, sort_by?, status_col?, out_col?}
  Within each group_by partition, label rows with the
  '<prev_status> → <status>' transition that produced them.
  Used for order-lifecycle narratives.

